lemma ofFunWithOrder_ae_congr {f f' : E → F} {μ : Measure E} (h : f =ᵐ[μ.restrict Ω] f') :
  ofFunWithOrder Ω n f μ = ofFunWithOrder Ω n f' μ := by
  -- We need to show that the distributions of f and f' are equal.
  -- This can be achieved by showing that their actions on any test function are equal.
  -- Since f and f' are equal almost everywhere on Ω, their integrals against any test function will be equal.
  -- Therefore, the distributions induced by f and f' will be equal.
